-- Romanian Utility Plans to Upgrade Southern Water, Sewage Network
-- B y   I r i n a   S a v u
-- 2013-03-13T15:39:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-13/romanian-utility-plans-to-upgrade-southern-water-sewage-network.html
Romanian utility  Cia de Apa Oltenia
SA  plans to upgrade and expand the water and sewage network in
southern  Romania  under a contract estimated at 67.3 million lei
($20 million).  The company plans to upgrade the water infrastructure in
the southern towns of Bechet, Calarasi and Dabuleni under a 12-
month contract, according to a European  procurement document 
published today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Irina Savu in Bucharest at 
 isavu@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  